exception of his WHIP which has steadily gotten worse each year).

Also, how often to you hear or read about ANY of the Giants pitchers
complimenting Righetti on helping them become better pitchers?  In the
past, Giants pitchers used to regularly give props to the pitching coach
for helping them become better pitchers, but since Righetti arrived nary
a good word is said about him by the pitchers.

(The only person who regularly compliments Righetti is Mike Krukow, but
he likes EVERYBODY.)

While Righetti might not be the number one problem with the Giants
pitching staff, he is definitely not part of the solution, IMHO.

