Wow.  Lowry was so bad last year that I couldn't believe his WHIP was worse
this year, so I had to look it up.  Of course, you're right.  But it's
interesting that while his WHIP has gone up each year, his ERA has gone down
each year (except last year).  I don't know what this means, or if it has
anything to do with Rag.  What I do know is that he used to get his
strikeouts with his changeup and his changeup has gone progressively
ineffective each year.  He's changed the way he pitch, more curve and less
changeup, I think.

I'm one of Lowry's biggest fans, so I'm very happy he's doing so well this
year.  Yet I don't really understand why he's doing so well right now with
the stuff he has, and think he could easily blow up next year.  So while I'd
*hate* to trade him, I think it *might* be a good idea.  But that really
depends on what we can get back, because he's so inexpensive and doesn't
really hurt the team in terms of salary at all.  I'm afraid the chances are
we'd get some crap back for him and he'll become an outstanding pitcher in a
different uniform.  That would really suck!
